<p>The questions are these: Do you oppose the deaths of innocent people? Are you willing to make personal sacrifices to stop it? Whether you think someone has a moral duty to prevent innocent people from being killed or whether someone is culpable for not intervening are up to you.</p>

<p>Similarly, are you seriously maintaining that promoting an &#8220;incentive to compete&#8221; and preventing &#8220;congealing layers of bureaucracy&#8221; are more important than the lives of millions?</p>

